      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The ground state has one arch and the second state has two lobes with a node at the center. Each state by itself only gains a global phase, so its magnitude squared stays fixed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.67,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 6,
      "narration_text": "How can adding two unchanging densities produce motion?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 3.82,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The mistake is adding densities. Quantum mechanics adds amplitudes first: psi equals c one phi one e to minus i E one t over h bar plus c two phi two e to minus i E two t over h bar.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.78,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Squaring that sum gives the two stationary densities plus a cross term. That interference term carries the changing relative phase between the two energies.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "expand"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.13,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The relative phase advances at angular frequency E two minus E one over h bar. When its cosine is positive, interference adds probability on one side and removes it from the other.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "rotate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.69,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Half a beat later, the cosine changes sign. The side that gained probability now loses it, and the density leans the opposite way.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "morph"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.87,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Over a full beat period, the density rocks left, becomes symmetric, rocks right, and returns. The walls do not push it; interference redistributes probability inside the box.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "slosh"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.33,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "The expectation value of position oscillates around the box center for this odd-even pair. Its frequency is set by the energy gap, not by either energy alone.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.71,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Yet the probabilities of measuring E one or E two remain constant. The average energy is fixed because only their relative phase changes.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.87,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "If the state contains only one energy, there is no second phase clock and no beat term. Motion in the density requires coherent superposition of different energies with overlapping spatial structure.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "qualify"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.88,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:55:00"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "Each eigenstate is stationary. Their relative phase is not. The interference term turns two fixed patterns into one sloshing probability cloud.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.92,
      "build": {
